nodes.text: Some theorize that T-Rex was actually a scavenger that didn't chase anything down because it had a very large area in the brain for processing odors.

Well that's interesting. I hadn't heard of that. Are there any other clues to suggest this dinosaur was a scavenger? I was surprised to learn that most birds have a poor sense of smell, except for the scavenger birds. They instead rely a good deal on their sight.
